An employee pumps petrol into a vehicle at a petrol station. AFP/Federico Parra JOHANNESBURG - Motorists can expect a record price hike in fuel next week. That's according to estimates from the Automobile Association.
Petrol is set for a massive increase of 73 cents a litre, diesel may see a 39 cents jump, and paraffin up by 37 cents. READ: Mbalula: Motorists will be informed on e-tolls soon But that is before additional April fuel levies kick in. When one factors in the levies, petrol could rise by as much as R1 a litre and diesel by 66 cents a litre. The higher international price of oil is the main reason behind the hike.